
Checked :
-->Occur at compile-time.
-->Compiler checks for checked exceptions
-->If Checked exceptions aren't handled/ignored, we will get a compile-time error.
-->Sub-class of exception class, doesn't inherit Runtime exception class

Eg: IOException, FileNotFoundException

UnChecked :
-->Occur at run-time.
--> Compiler doesn't check for unchecked exception.
-->If Unchecked exceptions aren't handled/, we will get a run-time error.
-->Sub-Class of RunTime exception class.

Eg: ArithmeticException, NullPointer Exception, Array/String IndexOutOfBounds Exception.